    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I agree that framing DEI as \"dismantling systemic barriers\" can alienate customers who view it as a political stance rather than a business strategy. For a boutique coffee shop, a neutral, business-focused approach is far more effective and inclusive.\n\nHere are three caption options that focus on community, culture, and shared values:\n\n**Option 1: Focus on Community**\n\"Great coffee starts with great people. We are dedicated to fostering an environment where everyone feels welcome and valued. Join us in building a community where diversity thrives and everyone belongs. ☕️✨ #DiversityMatters #SmallBusiness #InclusiveCulture\"\n\n**Option 2: Focus on Shared Values**\n\"True equity means listening to everyone. We're here to create a welcoming space for all backgrounds and perspectives. Let's make a difference together by supporting a diverse and inclusive community. 🌍💼 #DEI #CoffeeShop #CommunityFirst\"\n\n**Option 3: Focus on Growth**\n\"Great coffee starts with great people. We are committed to creating a space where every voice matters and every customer feels seen. Let's build a community defined by genuine inclusion and mutual respect. 🌱☕️ #",
